git commit

IF code you are writing and you want save the change-->create commitid

git reset --soft / --hard / --mixed

a commit id abc
b commit id def

it will drop the latest commit id, and take the code changes to the staging area

--mixed-->File will be completely tracked not in the staging area

--hard-->changes are deleted

reset 

--soft means you are droping the commit id, and changes are in the staging are
--hard means you are dropping the commit id and changes both
--mixed mean you ard dropping the commit id and changes are still there but untracked

reset-->commit id in git log command where head was pointing, was available in log in the log command or not??

